  <Subject Subject_ID="300219550">
    <Parent_Relationships>
      <Preferred_Parent>
        <Parent_Subject_ID>300219257</Parent_Subject_ID>
        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>vehicle groupings [300219257], object groupings by specific context [300241512], object groupings [300241507], Object Groupings and Systems (hierarchy name) [300241489], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Use both for groups of merchant or naval auxilliary ships traveling under armed escort and for groups of motor vehicles organized for the purpose of control and orderly movement, with or without escort protection.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000012041/DOD Dictionary of Military and Associated Terms (1987)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Úsese para ambos grupos de barcos auxiliares mercantiles o navales que viajan bajo escolta armada y para grupos de vehículos motorizados organizados con el propósito de controlar y ordenar el movimiento, con o son protección de escolta.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wordt zowel gebruikt voor groepen handels- of hulpschepen die varen onder gewapende begeleiding, als voor groepen motorvoertuigen die zijn georganiseerd voor controle en geordende vooruitgang, met of zonder beschermende begeleiding.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099099/Van Dale groot woordenboek (1994)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Bezeichnet sowohl Handels- oder Unterstützungsschiffe einer Kriegsflotte, die im Verband unterwegs sind und zuweilen durch Marineeinheiten eskortiert werden, wie auch eine Gruppe von Motorfahrzeugen, die aus Gründen der Kontrolle und des geordneten Vorwärtskommens mit oder ohne Eskorte gemeinschaftlich bewegt werden.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
